Last updated: January 2026

Notely respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how information is handled when you use the Notely application.

⸻

1. Information We Collect

Notely does not require account creation and does not directly collect personal information such as name, email address, or phone number.

All reminders, notes, and preferences created by the user are stored locally on the device.

⸻

2. Local Notifications

Notely uses local notifications to remind users of scheduled tasks.
	•	Notifications are created and managed entirely on the user’s device
	•	No notification data is transmitted to any server

⸻

3. Advertising & Third-Party Services

Notely displays banner and interstitial advertisements using Google AdMob, a third-party advertising service.

Google AdMob may automatically collect certain device-level information, including:
	•	Device identifiers (such as advertising identifiers)
	•	Advertising interaction data
	•	Usage data related to advertisements

This data may be used by Google for:
	•	Displaying advertisements
	•	Measuring ad performance
	•	Fraud prevention and security

Notely does not have access to or control over the data collected by Google AdMob.

Users can permanently remove all advertisements by purchasing the “Remove Ads” one-time in-app purchase.

⸻

4. Internet Usage

Notely works offline for core features such as creating and managing reminders.

An internet connection may be required for:
	•	Displaying advertisements
	•	Processing in-app purchases
	•	Loading third-party advertising services

⸻

5. In-App Purchases

Notely offers a one-time, non-consumable in-app purchase that removes advertisements permanently.

All payments are processed securely by Apple. Notely does not collect or store payment information.

⸻

6. App Tracking Transparency

Notely complies with Apple’s App Tracking Transparency (ATT) framework.

When required, users are asked for permission before tracking-related data is accessed. Tracking preferences can be managed at any time through iOS system settings.

⸻

7. Data Sharing

Notely does not sell or trade user data.

Limited data may be processed by third-party services (such as Google AdMob) solely for advertising and measurement purposes, in accordance with their privacy policies.

⸻

8. Data Security

All user-generated data is stored locally on the device.

Reasonable technical measures are implemented to protect the app and its data.

⸻

9. Children’s Privacy

Notely does not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13.

If you believe a child has provided personal information, please contact us so appropriate action can be taken.

⸻

10. Changes to This Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time.
Any changes will be reflected within the app or on the App Store product page.

⸻

11. Contact

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact:

Email: 6353ww@gmail.com
